- jwt-simple module is the 3rd party module used to maintain the Authentication in Node Applications.

- jwt-simple module is the Token Based Authentication System.

- By using jwt-simple module we can create the "tokens"

- making the readable data to unreadable data called as Token.

- we can either encrypt or decrypt the data by using jwt-simple module.

Ex.
var jwt = require("jwt-simple");

var token = jwt.encode({"u_name":"admin"},"tcs@admin.com");


console.log( jwt.decode(token,"tcs@admin.com") );

    // {"u_name":"admin"}